questions.title: * Caution! Do you have pain or other symptoms when you cough or sneeze during a bowel movement? Or, do you have back pain associated with bowel or bladder problems, pain or other symptoms when you cough or sneeze during a bowel movement or numbness in the groin area? If so, you should not take this test. Symptoms may represent a serious medical condition called Cauda Equina Syndrome which is typically a medical emergency. We strongly recommend that you seek medical assistance immediately. *
* Caution! Have you recently felt faint or experienced any shortness of breath? *
Have you been in the hospital recently or have you had a medical procedure, and not been medically released to perform normal activities? *
1. What's the distance of the head to the wall? *
2.  Are you shoulders "rolled" forward towards your chest? *
3. Are your neck and head aligned in a straight line with spine? *
4a. When you look straight up, do you feel any pain? *
4b.  When you look down, do you feel pain? *
4c.  When you look down to the floor, is your chin touching your chest? *
4d. When you look down to the floor, do you feel an electric like sensation down the spine, arms , or legs? *
5a.  When you turn your head to the left, do you feel pain with this movement? *
5b.  When you turn your head to the left, is your head even with your shoulder? *
6a.  When you turn your head to the right, do you feel pain with this movement? *
6b.  When you turn your head to the right, is your head even with your shoulder? *
7.  When you turn your head to the right, is your rotation equal on both sides? *
8a. When you tilt your left ear towards your left shoulder . Does it cause you pain? *
8b. When you tilt your left ear to your left shoulder, did you hear popping or grinding sounds? *
8c. When you tilt your left ear towards your left shoulder, does it cause tingling? *
9a. When you tilt your right ear towards your right shoulder . Does it cause you pain?  *
9b. When you tilt your Right ear towards your Right shoulder, did you feel and/or hear popping or grinding sounds? *
9c. When you tilt your right ear towards your right  shoulder, does it cause  tingling? *
9d. Tilt your head to the left and right.  Did you feel pain when tilting your head to either side? *
9e.  When you tilt your head to the left and right, can you tilt your head evenly to both sides? *
9f. Do you feel and/or hear popping or grinding sounds during these head movements? *
10a.  When you reach both arms over your head, do you feel pain? *
11.  When you perform elbow flexion, do you feel pain?  If "Yes", where do you feel the most pain? *
12a. With your left hand on you right shoulder and your left elbow on your chest, do you feel pain or tingling? *
12b. When performing this movement, does your elbow touch your chest? *
13a.  With your right hand on you left shoulder and your right elbow on your chest, do you feel pain or tingling? *
13b. When performing this movement, does your elbow touch your chest? *
14a. Do you feel pain when you reach your right hand behind your head to touch your left shoulder blade? *
14b. Can you touch your right  hand to your upper  left shoulder blade? *
15a.  Do you feel pain when you reach your left hand behind your head to touch your right shoulder blade? *
15b.  Can you touch your left hand to your upper right shoulder blade? *
16.  Can both hands reach equally the same distance when performing step 14 and 15? *
17a.  Do you feel pain when you slide your right hand up the lower part of your back? *
17b.  Can you touch your right  hand to your lower left shoulder blade? *
18a.  Do you feel pain when you slide your left hand up the lower part of your back? *
18b. Can you touch your left hand to your lower right shoulder blade? *
19.  Can both hands reach equally as high when performing Step 17 and 18? *
20.  Can you complete the directions given above? *
21a.  When you slide both hands down the back of your neck at the same time, do you feel pain? *
21b.  Can you slide both hands down the back of your neck an equal distance? *
22a.  When you rotate your hands, do you feel pain? *
22b.  When you rotate your hands, can you rotate them equally on both sides? *
23.  When you rotate your hands, do you feel and/or hear popping or grinding sounds during your arm movements? *
24a.  While your hands are in this prayer like position, do you feel pain, numbness or tingling in your forearms, wrists, hands or fingers? *
24b.  While your hands are in this prayer like position, are your arms parallel with the floor? *
24c.  While your hands are in this prayer like position, are they equal on both sides? *
25a.  While your hands are in this reverse prayer position, do you feel pain, numbness or tingling in your forearms, wrists, hands or fingers? *
25b.  While your hands are in this reverse prayer position, can you bring your forearms parallel to the floor? *
26.  As you follow the directions above, do you feel pain in your left hand? *
27.  As you follow the directions above, do you feel pain in your right hand? *
28.Did you hear and/or feel popping or grinding sounds during your hand movements? *

29a.  With your left hand on the front of your left leg, what is the distance from the tip of left middle finger to the floor?
                                *

29b.  With your right hand on the front of your right leg, what is the distance from the tip of right middle finger to the floor?
                                *

30a.  Slide both hands down the front of your leg, then measure the distance from your left middle fingertip to the floor while keeping your knees locked.
                                *

30b.  Slide both hands down the front of your leg, then measure the distance from your right middle fingertip to the floor while keeping your knees locked.
                                *

31.  With your left hand on the outside of  your left leg, measure the distance from the tip of your left middle fingertip to the floor.
                                *

32.  While keeping your legs straight, slide your left hand down the side of  your left leg, then measure the distance from the tip of your left middle fingertip to the floor.
                                *

33.  With your right hand on the outside of  your right leg, measure the distance from the tip of your right middle fingertip to the floor.
                                *

34.  While keeping your legs straight, slide your right hand down the side of  your right leg, then measure the distance from the tip of your right middle fingertip to the floor.
                                *

Do you have more pain bending to the left or right? *

37b.  While completing these directions, did you experience low back pain with your left leg straight? *

37d.  While completing these directions, did you experience pain in your buttocks with your left leg straight? *
37e.  While completing these directions, did you experience thigh pain with your right leg straight? *
37f. While completing the directions above, did you experience THIGH pain with your left leg straight? *
37g. While completing the directions above, did you experience KNEE pain with your right leg straight? *
37h. While completing the directions above, did you experience KNEE pain with your left leg straight? *
37i. While completing the directions above, did you experience FOOT pain with your right leg straight? *
37j. While completing the directions above, did you experience FOOT pain with your left leg straight? *
37k. Do you feel any tingling or numbness? If yes, where? *
38.  With both legs straight, do you feel any stretching or tightening in your muscles or pain or tingling? *
39.  With both legs straight, cough - When you follow the directions for this movement, do you feel any pain, numbness or tingling? *
40.  While sitting in a chair, extend both legs straight, lean forward & cough -Do you feel any pain, numbness or tingling? *
41.  When you follow these directions, do you feel any pain? *
